Section 1:
1 L.D. 34
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 EDUCATION AND CULTURAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 53, L.D. 34, “An Act to Increase the
10 Minimum Salary for Teachers”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 3. 20-A MRSA §13408 is enacted to read:
13 §13408. Minimum salaries beginning in 2026-2027 school year
14 Each school administrative unit shall establish a minimum salary for certified teachers
15 and career and technical education teachers in accordance with this section. The
16 commissioner shall establish a minimum salary for certified teachers and career and
17 technical education teachers employed at a school, career and technical education center or
18 career and technical education region located in the unorganized territory in accordance
19 with this section:
20 1. School year 2026-2027. For the school year starting after June 30, 2026, the
21 minimum salary is $45,000;
22 2. School year 2027-2028. For the school year starting after June 30, 2027, the
23 minimum salary is $47,500; and
24 3. School year 2028-2029. For the school year starting after June 30, 2028, the
25 minimum salary is $50,000.
26 A school administrative unit shall provide to the department annually on or before
27 October 1st the number of certified teachers and career and technical education teachers
28 eligible for incremental salary increases as defined in section 15689, subsection 7‑A,
29 paragraph A.'
30 Amend the bill in section 4 in subsection 7-A in the first blocked paragraph in the first
31 line (page 2, line 29 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "2028" and inserting the
32 following: '2030'
33 Amend the bill by inserting after section 4 the following:
Page 1 - 132LR0233(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 53, L.D. 34
1 'Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
2 allocations are made.
3 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
4 General Purpose Aid for Local Schools 0308
5 Initiative: Provides funds to increase the minimum annual salary for certified teachers and
6 career and technical education teachers from $40,000 in fiscal year 2025-26 to $45,000 in
7 fiscal year 2026-27, $47,500 in fiscal year 2027-28 and $50,000 in fiscal year 2028-29.
8 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
9 All Other $0 $5,733,838
10 __________ __________
11 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $0 $5,733,838
128 General Purpose Aid for Local Schools 0308
13 Initiative: Provides ongoing funds for the increase in employer contributions related to the
14 normal cost component of the Maine Public Employees Retirement System due to the
15 increase in salaries for certain certified teachers and career and technical education
16 teachers.
17 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
18 All Other $0 $249,995
19 __________ __________
20 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $0 $249,995
2117
22 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
23 DEPARTMENT TOTALS 2025-26 2026-27
24
25 GENERAL FUND $0 $5,983,833
26 __________ __________
27 DEPARTMENT TOTAL - ALL FUNDS $0 $5,983,833
2282 '
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment removes provisions related to minimum teacher salary after school
3333 year 2028-2029 proposed in the bill. The amendment also clarifies that teachers in the
3344 unorganized territory are subject to minimum salary requirements and extends the repeal
3355 date of the provision of law governing the funding adjustments for minimum teacher
3366 salaries to July 1, 2030.
3377 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3388 (See attached)
